main event: Multiple unidentified flying objects were sighted in Avoca, Wisconsin on October 8, 1960.
interesting points: The objects were described as oblong or oval in shape with a horizontal row of colored lights (red and green)., The sighting lasted for about 10 minutes., The objects appeared to change course and altitude during the observation., The event was reported by an unidentified witness and several other persons., The Air Force classified this as an unexplained aerial phenomenon.
witness description: an unidentified person and several others
